{
  "texts": [
    "This layer employs a transformation matrix T that maps modality-specific features into a unified semantic space.",
    "The transformation for a modality m can be described by the equation:v ′ m = σ(T m v m + b m)where v m represents the input features from modality m, T m is the transformation matrix for modality m, b m is a bias vector, and σ denotes a non-linear activation function such as the Rectified Linear Unit (ReLU).Additionally, adjustments are made to the attention mechanisms within each expert, allowing them to better recognize and weight modal-specific features relevant to the tasks at hand.",
    "This is achieved through a modality-aware attention mechanism, which adjusts the attention weights based on the type of input modality:α m i,j = exp(β • tanh(W m h i + U m h j)) N k=1 exp(β • tanh(W m h i + U m h k))where h i and h j are the hidden states of the elements i and j in the sequence, W m and U m are weight matrices specific to modality m, α m i,j are the attention weights, N is the number of elements in the sequence, and β is a scaling factor that adjusts the sharpness of the attention distribution.These architectural enhancements are designed to facilitate a more seamless integration of text, image, and audio data, leading to a more coherent and context-aware output.",
    "The model's capability to adaptively process and integrate these different modalities is expected to enhance its overall performance and applicability across various multimodal tasks.",
    "Data Fusion TechniquesIn the modified Mistral 8x7B architecture, we implement advanced data fusion techniques that enable dynamic integration of multimodal information."
  ]
}